  "prompt": "How should I handle a telephone interview?",
  "response": "Here are some tips for handling a telephone interview successfully:\n\n1. Preparation\n- Research the company beforehand\n- Review the job description\n- Prepare potential answers to common interview questions\n- Have your resume and notes nearby\n- Keep a glass of water close\n\n2. Technical setup\n- Use a landline if possible for better sound quality\n- Choose a quiet location with good reception\n- Charge your phone or have it plugged in\n- Use a headset or speakerphone for clear audio\n\n3. During the interview\n- Answer the phone professionally\n- Speak clearly and with enthusiasm\n- Listen carefully to questions\n- Take brief notes if needed\n- Sit up straight and smile (it changes your tone of voice)\n- Avoid background noise and distractions\n\n4. Communication tips\n- Use the interviewer's name\n- Provide concise, focused answers\n- Ask thoughtful questions about the role\n- Show enthusiasm for the position\n- Use positive, confident language\n\n5. Follow-up\n- Send a thank-you email within 24 hours\n- Reiterate your interest in the position\n- Reference specific discussion points from the interview\n\nRemember to be prepared, professional, and confident throughout the call.",
